        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-20 18:51:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nLooks like this is triggered for every patch submitted. That would create a long turnaround time for each patch. Lets do this every hour or every 6 hours or something like that using a timed trigger.\nWe don't want each patch to be gated by a long running jenkins job.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8644624098052d4a9f9db62100bacff588990e95",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-21 05:06:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Looks like this is triggered for every patch submitted. That would create a long turnaround time for each patch. Lets do this every hour or every 6 hours or something like that using a timed trigger.\n> We don't want each patch to be gated by a long running jenkins job.\n\nNot sure but I think it's not gating you. People with +2 rights can merge patch regardless this verify job currently running? And considering normal review practices, there's plenty of time review is open and job to give feedback.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
